      "description": "searchmode -  - Controls how searching for blobs is done across all the points.\n\n all - All the points are compared against each other to find blobs. This mode is slower but more robust for data that has the points randomly assorted in the . consecutive - Points are only compared against points in neighbouring samples of the  data to find blobs. This is much faster but the data much be setup such that points that are close to each other in space are next to each other in the  samples. Data coming from devices such as the Hokuyo CHOP and Leuze ROD4 CHOP output data in this format.",
